      * Representation on the XSEDE User Advisory Body - Frank. I have attended one XSEDE User advisory meeting. It was a useful experience to better understand the issues XSEDE, and its users, faces,  as well as how XSEDE operates. It's also allowing me to learn about their culture.
      * Other 
   * PKI update - Von Welch
      * Current status – transition phase
         * Started transition phase as of Oct 1 -To complete by Feb 2013. Goals:
            * Establish RAs for all OSG VOs and Grid Admins for all OSG domains by mid-December
            * All users able and encouraged to use OSG PKI by mid-January 2013
      * Current activities
         * Training and Enrolling RAs and Grid Admins – Working out process kinks
         * Software improvements/fixes/packaging -Discovering features we need, Uncovering bugs, Usability tweaks.  Command-line client RPM
         * Documentation and preparing for end users
      * Planned activities for transition phase
         * Presenting Contingency Plan to WLCG Management Board for comment on Oct 16th
         * Dry-runs of audit procedures, contingency procedures
         * Working closely with Ops team to transition support
         * Complete in progress transition command-line clients to SW team
      * Reminder for info:
         * Public page: -https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Security/OSGCATransition2012
         * Training sessions: -https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Security/OSGPKITraining
         * Weekly call info and notes: - https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Operations/OSGPKITransitionCallNotes
